<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Baker</persName>, chargé.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-14"><hi rend="italic">October 14,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Have Nicaragua and Salvador ratified union of June, 1895? If so, does the
                            Diet take charge of their diplomatic affairs? Minister to Guatemala
                            telegraphs that Honduras has abolished foreign office, turning over
                            international relations to Diet.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>